On Friday, a group of 31 boys assaulted and overpowered staff members in an attempt to escape. CAPE TOWN Police are still tracking three boys who escaped from the Bonnytoun Secure Care Centre over the weekend.Chaos erupted at the child and youth care facility in Kraaifontein on Friday when a group of 31 boys assaulted and overpowered staff members in an attempt to escape.Two officials were injured.Social Development MEC Albert Fritz earlier today visited one of them who remains in hospital.Spokesperson, Sihle Ngobese says operations at Bonnytoun have returned to normal. The MEC checked on the colleagues who were injured during the incident and wished them well. (Edited by Refilwe Pitjeng)